A man from  Northern Ireland  was
charged and appeared in court today in relation to a number of
terrorism offenses, including possessing firearms and
explosives, Dublin-based broadcaster RTE  reported .  The arms seizure was made by detectives investigating the
murder of Northern Irish policeman, Ronan Kerr, according to the
report. Kerr was killed by a car bomb on April 2.  Officials from the Northern Ireland Police Service and
